						<h3 class="ec-service__title">Warehouse &amp; Fulfillment Operations</h3>
						<p class="ec-service__tagline">Know what's in which bin, zone, or location &mdash; at all times.</p>
						<div class="ec-service__block">
							<h4 class="ec-service__block-title">The problem this solves</h4>
							<p>Multi-location brands (DTC warehouse + 3PL + wholesale stock + returns staging) lose track of where inventory actually sits. "We have 300 units" becomes meaningless when 180 are at the 3PL, 80 are staged for a wholesale order, 30 are returns awaiting inspection, and 10 are missing entirely.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="ec-service__block">
							<h4 class="ec-service__block-title">What we run</h4>
							<ul class="ec-service__list">
								<li><strong>Multi-location stock mapping</strong> &mdash; every SKU tracked by location, bin, or zone. One dashboard shows where every unit is.</li>
								<li><strong>3PL coordination and receiving</strong> &mdash; when inventory moves to your 3PL, we verify receipt matches the outbound manifest. Discrepancies get resolved before they become permanent.</li>
								<li><strong>Transfer management</strong> &mdash; moving stock between locations is tracked as a formal transfer, not an email. Units in transit are visible as "in-flight" so you don't double-sell.</li>
								<li><strong>Wholesale allocation</strong> &mdash; for brands doing both DTC and wholesale, we split inventory allocation so a big wholesale PO doesn't accidentally stock out your hero SKU on Shopify during a key weekend.</li>
								<li><strong>Cycle counts and variance investigation</strong> &mdash; rotating counts by bin or zone. Variances over threshold get investigated, not just written off.</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="ec-service__block">
							<h4 class="ec-service__block-title">The outcome</h4>
							<p>You stop selling phantom inventory. You stop over-allocating to wholesale. Your 3PL billing matches what they're actually holding. Your returns stop disappearing into a pile nobody looks at.</p>
